The paper discusses the use of natural language queries for information retrieval from databases, which falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a multi-level knowledge-based middleware that uses a concept reasoner and a query strategy engine, which are techniques commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of structured query language and the difficulty in mapping natural language queries to it, which is a problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
